FuncDef:
The end-global-value command concludes the configuration of a global variable set, exits the global variable set view, and returns to the system view.
By default, no filtering policy is configured.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
A global variable set is a group of frequently used values that are defined as global variables. Global variables can be referenced by all route-filters configured on a device. To conclude the configuration of a global variable set, exit the global variable set view, and return to the system view, run the end-global-value command.
Prerequisites
Elements have been configured for a global variable set.
